Section --- Managing Services

  We will see the usage of sc, the Windows Command Line Service controler utility.

  As an attacker we need to:

  - Determine what services are running
  - Attempt to disable antivirus
  - Modify existing services on a system


-- SERVICE CONTROLLER --

  Query, modify and manage host services locally and over the network.

  > sc --> Description of the command "SC is a command line program used for communicating with the Service Control Manager and services."


-- QUERY SERVICES --

  Get information such as the process state, process id (pid), and service type.

  > sc query type= service --> List all services are currently actively running on the system
  (Respect the sparce)

  > sc query windefend --> Querying for Windows Defender

  > sc stop windefend --> Trying to stopping the service Windows Defender 
  (sc stop <service name>)

  This service is protected under stricter access requierement than what local administratos accounts have.

  The only thing that can stop and start the Defender service is the SYSTEM machine account.


-- Stopping Services --

  >sc query Spooler --> Querying the Print Spooler service

  >sc stop Spooler 


-- Starting Services --

  >sc start Spooler  


-- Modifying Services --

  >sc query windefend